---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const effectiveDate = "May 15, 2026";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Campus XI Terms of Use including purchases, passes, refund rules, and social card usage limits."
>
  <section class="hero-panel hero-panel--compact">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="meta">Effective date: {effectiveDate}</p>
      <p class="hero-text">
        By using Campus XI, users agree to these terms. If they do not agree,
        they should not use the app.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell legal-shell">
    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>What Campus XI Is</h2>
      <p>
        Campus XI is a fantasy football application that allows organizers to
        host events and allows users to join, build squads, earn points, follow
        leaderboards, and use event-related premium features.
      </p>
      <p>
        Features, scoring rules, event formats, prizes, and premium tools may
        vary by event, tournament, or app update.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Accounts and Acceptable Use</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Users are responsible for keeping their sign-in credentials secure.</li>
        <li>Users must provide accurate account and team information.</li>
        <li>Users are responsible for activity carried out through their account.</li>
        <li>Users must not misuse the app, interfere with events, exploit bugs, or attempt fraud.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Gameplay, Scoring, and Leaderboards</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Users may build teams and participate in organizer-hosted events.</li>
        <li>Points, rankings, and leaderboard results are determined by the app's event logic and rules.</li>
        <li>Organizers may set event-specific conditions, subject to the app's available features.</li>
        <li>Campus XI may correct obvious scoring, ranking, or technical errors where necessary.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Passes and Premium Access</h2>
      <p>
        Campus XI may offer premium passes, including Bronze, Silver, and Gold
        tiers. These passes may unlock premium tools and features, including
        performance-related tools such as squad insight or similar premium
        utilities described in the app at the time of purchase.
      </p>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Pass access is granted after successful purchase and verification.</li>
        <li>Pass features, pricing, and packaging may change over time.</li>
        <li>Premium tools are intended to assist users but do not guarantee better results, prizes, or leaderboard outcomes.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Gift Purchases and Codes</h2>
      <p>
        Campus XI may allow users to buy eligible passes or gifts for another
        person. In those cases, the purchase may generate a code that can be
        shared and redeemed by another user on their own account.
      </p>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Gift codes may be single-use and may be subject to validation rules.</li>
        <li>Users are responsible for sending gift codes to the intended recipient.</li>
        <li>Campus XI may cancel, block, or investigate codes tied to fraud, abuse, or verification issues.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Upgrades</h2>
      <p>
        Campus XI may allow users to upgrade from one pass tier to a higher
        tier. Where offered, upgrade pricing may reflect the difference between
        the current eligible pass value and the higher-tier pass price, rather
        than charging full price again.
      </p>
      <p>
        Upgrade availability, pricing logic, and eligibility may change over
        time.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Refunds and Purchase Problems</h2>
      <p>
        If a purchase is completed and verification is successful, the purchase
        is generally non-refundable except where required by law or required by
        the relevant app store or payment provider.
      </p>
      <p class="notice">
        If a purchase goes through but verification fails, the user should
        contact support at <a href="mailto:support@campusxi.com"
          >support@campusxi.com</a
        > for assistance or refund review.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Saved Cards and Shared Content</h2>
      <p>
        Users may generate and save performance cards or similar shareable
        visuals to their own device gallery. Those saves happen at the user's
        request.
      </p>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Saved cards are for personal use unless Campus XI expressly allows something broader.</li>
        <li>Users must not use the app to impersonate others or misuse Campus XI branding.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Availability, Bugs, and Support</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Campus XI may update, suspend, or discontinue features at any time.</li>
        <li>We do not guarantee uninterrupted service or error-free operation.</li>
        <li>Third-party outages, store issues, or payment verification problems may affect access.</li>
        <li>Users should contact support for purchase issues, code issues, or technical problems.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Disclaimers and Limits</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Campus XI provides fantasy football tools and event participation features, not guaranteed outcomes.</li>
        <li>Premium tools may improve decision-making but do not promise winnings, prizes, or ranking success.</li>
        <li>To the fullest extent allowed by law, Campus XI is not responsible for indirect or consequential losses arising from use of the app.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms of Use from time to time. Continued use of
        Campus XI after updated terms take effect means the user accepts the
        revised terms.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms can be sent to
        <a href="mailto:support@campusxi.com">support@campusxi.com</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
